extend ../../partials/issue

block append config
  - page.title = "Migration Policy"

block intro-image
  img.bg-img(data-src="../../img/migration-policy.jpg")

block intro-caption
  :marked
    Photo: Ryan Pierse/Getty

block intro-description
  :marked
    Australia is a growing nation with a sizable migrant population, but the
    issue of how many migrants to take and where to take them from has been
    long contested. With our sustained population growth year on year made
    possible by immigrants, successive governments have had to balance the
    clear economic and social benefits of migration with concerns about
    overcrowding and service delivery.

