      .col-1-2.bg-dk.txt-ff
        .p-md
          .pv-xs.txt-sm.txt-tu.txt-hl= page.title
          .txt-xxl.pv-xs The Government

      .col-1-2.p-md.bg-dk.txt-ff
        .txt-md.txt-border.ph-md.txt-left(style="max-width: 460px")
          :marked
            The Liberal Party has pledged to cap permanent migration at 160,000
            a year for the next four years, the previous cap was 190,000. In
            addition it will introduce a new skilled worker visa program for
            23,000 migrants requiring them to spend 3 years in regional
            Australia to earn permanent residency.  Redistributing migrants to
            regional Australia to reduce congestion in major cities has been a
            major Coalition policy.
 
